Ri Yong Ho told the World Organization’s General Assembly that North Korea had shown “significant goodwill” over the past year, for example by stopping nuclear and missile tests, unraveling a nuclear testing area and promising not to further develop nuclear weapons and nuclear technology.
"We have not seen a similar reaction from the United States," he said.
