Ri did not mention any more plans for a summit between Kim and Trump, which the U.S. leader highlighted at the UN earlier this week.
The minister instead highlighted three meetings between Kim and South Korean leader Moon Jae-in within the past five months, adding: "If nuclear weapons were to be negotiated with South Korea and not the United States, the negotiations would not be so tight."
Nonetheless, the tone in Ris’ speech was very different from last year’s, when he told the UN General Assembly that firing North Korea’s rockets against the U.S. mainland was inevitable, after “Mr. Evil President” Trump called Kim a “rocket man” on a suicide mission.
