According to the FWC, there are reports of widespread blooms in the area around Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Charlotte and Collier – suggesting that the concentration is decreasing.
The flowering of algae spreads over a coastline of 210 km from northern Pinellas County to southern Lee County.
There are smaller blooms about 16 km from the coast in Hillsborough County, but there are fewer than last week.
There are also blooms in Pasco County.
